#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 22"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "22. Atthaṅgatasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on gone down"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.54"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.22.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.273"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="517"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadanti pariyāyena."
msgstr "At that time the senior monks were instructing the nuns in turn,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato cūḷapanthakassa pariyāyo hoti bhikkhuniyo "
"ovadituṃ."
msgstr "and on one occasion it was the turn of Venerable Cūḷapanthaka."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The nuns said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"“na dāni ajja ovādo iddho bhavissati, taññeva dāni udānaṃ ayyo cūḷapanthako "
"punappunaṃ bhaṇissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Today the instruction won’t be effective, since Venerable Cūḷapanthaka will "
"just be repeating the same utterance over and over.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yenāyasmā cūḷapanthako tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards those nuns went to Cūḷapanthaka,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ cūḷapanthakaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho tā bhikkhuniyo āyasmā cūḷapanthako etadavoca—"
msgstr "Cūḷapanthaka then said to them,"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“samaggāttha, bhaginiyo”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you all present, Sisters?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“Samaggāmhāyyā”ti."
msgstr "“We’re all present, Venerable.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Vattanti, bhaginiyo, aṭṭha garudhammā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you keeping the eight rules to be respected?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "“Vattantāyyā”ti."
msgstr "“We are.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“Eso, bhaginiyo, ovādo”ti niyyādetvā imaṃ udānaṃ punappunaṃ abhāsi—"
msgstr ""
"After saying, “This is the instruction,” he spoke the same utterance again "
"and again:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="518"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Adhicetaso appamajjato,"
msgstr "“For the heedful one possessed of the higher mind,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Munino monapathesu sikkhato;"
msgstr "For the sage training on the path to sagacity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Sokā na bhavanti tādino,"
msgstr "There are no sorrows for such a one,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Upasantassa sadā satīmato”ti."
msgstr "The peaceful one, who is always mindful.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.274"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="519"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "And the nuns said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.19"
msgid ""
"“nanu avocumhā—na dāni ajja ovādo iddho bhavissati, taññeva dāni udānaṃ ayyo "
"cūḷapanthako punappunaṃ bhaṇissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Didn’t we say that the instruction wouldn’t be effective, that Venerable "
"Cūḷapanthaka would just be repeating the same utterance over and over?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr "But Cūḷapanthaka overheard that conversation between the nuns."

#. VAR: tañceva → taññeva (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako vehāsaṃ abbhuggantvā ākāse antalikkhe "
"caṅkamatipi tiṭṭhatipi nisīdatipi seyyampi kappeti dhūmāyatipi pajjalatipi "
"antaradhāyatipi, tañceva udānaṃ bhaṇati aññañca bahuṃ buddhavacanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"He then rose up into the air, walked back and forth in space, and he stood, "
"sat down, and lay down there. He emitted smoke and fire, and he disappeared, "
"all the while speaking the same utterance and many other sayings by the "
"Buddha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "And the nuns said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "“It’s astonishing and amazing!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"Na vata no ito pubbe ovādo evaṃ iddho bhūtapubbo yathā ayyassa "
"cūḷapanthakassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"No previous instruction has been as effective as this one from Venerable "
"Cūḷapanthaka!”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.25"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako tā bhikkhuniyo yāva samandhakārā ovaditvā "
"uyyojesi—"
msgstr ""
"And Cūḷapanthaka kept on instructing those nuns until the dark of night, and "
"then dismissed them, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti."
msgstr "“Go, Sisters.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="520"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo nagaradvāre thakite bahinagare vasitvā kālasseva "
"nagaraṃ pavisanti."
msgstr ""
"But because the gates to the town were closed, those nuns stayed the night "
"outside and entered in the morning."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "“abrahmacāriniyo imā bhikkhuniyo;"
msgstr "“These nuns aren’t celibate."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "ārāme bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ vasitvā idāni nagaraṃ pavisantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They spend the night in the monastery with the monks and only now do they "
"enter the town.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.55"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="521"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.31"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.32"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Cūḷapanthaka,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.34"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā cūḷapanthako atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadissatī”"
"ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Cūḷapanthaka instruct the nuns after the sun has set?”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.35"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Cūḷapanthaka, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.36"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.37"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.38"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadissasi."
msgstr "Cūḷapanthaka, how can you instruct the nuns after the sun has set?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.275"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.39"
msgid "Netaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without  it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.40"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.40a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
#. <span class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="522"></a> 
#. VAR: sūriye → suriye (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: Sammatopi ce → sammato ce pi (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.41"
msgid ""
"“Sammatopi ce bhikkhu atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Even if he has been agreed upon, if a monk instructs the nuns after sunset, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs1.42"
msgid "(<em>22</em>:<strong>71</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.21.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="523"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Sammato nāma"
msgstr "Who has been agreed upon:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "ñatticatutthena kammena sammato."
msgstr ""
"who has been agreed upon through a procedure consisting of one motion and "
"three announcements."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="524"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Atthaṅgate sūriyeti"
msgstr "After sunset:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "oggate sūriye."
msgstr "after the sun has gone down."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="525"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "The nuns:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "they have been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="526"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Ovadeyyāti"
msgstr "Instructs:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid ""
"aṭṭhahi vā garudhammehi aññena vā dhammena ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he instructs in the eight rules to be respected or he gives any other "
"teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.22.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="527"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Atthaṅgate atthaṅgatasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the sun has set, and he perceives that it has, and he instructs the nuns, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Atthaṅgate vematiko ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the sun has set, but he is unsure if it has, and he instructs the nuns, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Atthaṅgate anatthaṅgatasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the sun has set, but he perceives that it has not, and he instructs the "
"nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="528"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Anatthaṅgate atthaṅgatasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the sun has not set, but he perceives that it has, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Anatthaṅgate vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the sun has not set, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Anatthaṅgate anatthaṅgatasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If the sun has not set, and he perceives that it has not, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.22.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="529"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "uddesaṃ dento, paripucchaṃ dento,"
msgstr "if he gives a summary;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "“osārehi ayyā”ti vuccamāno,"
msgstr "if he questions them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "osāreti,"
msgstr "if he recites when asked to do so;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "pañhaṃ pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,"
msgstr "if he replies when asked a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ bhikkhuniyo suṇanti,"
msgstr ""
"if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is to a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is to a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.10"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.11"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="530"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:pts-cs2.3.12"
msgid "Atthaṅgatasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on gone down, is finished."

